{
  "stem": "4670.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He had no family anywhere.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He only had his mother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I took his address with me and he begged me to try and get him a visa.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And that's the last I heard of-- his name was Arnold Mischel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Anyway, we left finally in-- on October 29th, I believe it was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We left Bremerhaven.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And when I got aboard the ship, they looked- I had gotten this coat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I called it a teddy bear coat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It was like a fake fur and I loved it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And when I was stepping on board ship, and they said, wait, and they thought that I was hiding money inside there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they were going to cut the lining.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I cried and I asked them to please leave my coat alone.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they could feel there was nothing in it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I thought it was indignation to the last.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But once we got aboard ship, we felt we left Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "You really didn't because it was a German line.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "You couldn't get on any other European line.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We were on board a German ship.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "It was called the Europa.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "It was a sister ship of the Bremen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And we finally arrived in New York in-- on November 4th, 1930.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I never forget, when we passed the Statue of Liberty, we were all pressed together against the railing and everybody cried.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We did not stop at Ellis Island at that point, even though they were still stopping at Ellis Island, because a great many Americans were aboard ship and they didn't want to inconvenience them.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And then we were being held in a different area, because all the Americans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We were getting off the ship a little later.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And since my name was with a W, I knew it would be late.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
